# xv6 Custom System Calls (RISC-V)

## 📌 Project Overview
This project is based on the xv6 operating system (RISC-V version). The main objective is to understand the internal working of an operating system by implementing **custom system calls** and modifying kernel-level code.

xv6 is a teaching OS inspired by Unix Version 6. In this project, we extend its functionality by adding new system calls and exploring kernel-user interactions.

---

## 🎯 Objectives
- Understand the working of system calls
- Learn interaction between user space and kernel space
- Modify xv6 kernel safely
- Implement and test custom functionalities

---

## ⚙️ Features Implemented
- ✅ Added custom system calls
- ✅ Modified kernel files (`kernel/`)
- ✅ Updated system call handling (`syscall.c`, `defs.h`)
- ✅ Added user-level programs for testing
- ✅ Thread and mutex related changes (if applicable)

> ✨ Replace below with your actual syscalls:
- Example: `getpidcount` – counts active processes  
- Example: `setpriority` – changes process priority  

